  • Konstruktordetails

    • CustomPlayerSelector

      public CustomPlayerSelector(String action, String infoItemExtraInfos, PlayerMenuUtility playerMenuUtility, java.util.function.Function<T,R> functionToExecute, java.util.function.Function<Map.Entry<UUID,org.bukkit.event.inventory.InventoryAction>,org.bukkit.ChatColor> functionForDecidingItemColor, Menu oldMenu, List<org.bukkit.entity.Player> players, boolean multiSelect)
      This Constructor is used to set up a Custom Player Selector Menu.
      If you want to use Multi-Select, you need to have T as a Map<UUID, InventoryAction>.

      The following Values can be null if Multi-Select isn't enabled:
      - functionForDecidingItemColor
      Parameter:
      action - Info for the Player what the Menu is used for. (Example: "Select a Player to invite to your Guild")
      infoItemExtraInfos - Extra Infos for the Info Item. (Example: "(Green = Online, Red = Offline, Black = Inactive)")
      playerMenuUtility - The PlayerMenuUtility for the Menu.
      functionToExecute - The Function that should be executed after the Player selected a Player. (If Multi-Select is enabled, this will first be executed after the Player clicked the Confirm Button)
      functionForDecidingItemColor - The Function that should be executed to decide what Color the Name of the Player should have.
      oldMenu - The Menu that should be opened after the Player selected a Player.
      players - The List of Players that should be displayed in the Menu.
      multiSelect - If the Player should be able to select multiple Players.
